frameDefinitions: A Speaker succeeds in getting an Addressee to believe or plan to execute the Content the Speaker has in mind.
In this frame, there is a Part of a Whole in which the Part is defined with respect to the canonical or inherent orientation of the Whole.
A Place is located far off from centers of population, culture, and/or trade.
This frame contains  words for Individuals as viewed in terms of their vocation.
An individual or organization, the Front, serves as a cover for an Illicit_activity or an Illicit_organization.
An Agent behaves as if they were a particular individual or type of Simulated_entity with the intent of misleading observers of their behavior.
frameExamples: At one point, Walter tries to <t>convince</t> his wife that he has had a story accepted by BBC Radio.
The laundromat is a <t>front</t> for the Yakuza.
The belfast bank robbers <t>posed</t> as police.
listRoleDefinitions: The person that the Speaker seeks to influence to act.
The person who intends through the use of language to get another person to act.
The wish for action on the <fen>Addressee</fen>'s part that the <fen>Speaker</fen> expresses.
A piece of written or spoken material that changes the mind of the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The general item or items that are the focus of the <fen>Content</fen> of the <fen>Speaker</fen>'s message.
When the <fen>Speaker</fen> suades the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The location where the Speaker suades the Addressee.
A piece of a larger <fen>Whole</fen>.
An undivided entity having all its <fen>Part</fen>s.
The town or area that is in a remote location.
The <fen>Person</fen> is the human being.
The <fen>Front</fen> acts as a legitimate individual, organization, or enterprise, but is truly a cover for an illicit organization or activity.
The existence and activities of the <fen>Illicit_organization</fen> are concealed by the <fen>Front</fen>.
The <fen>Illicit_activity</fen> of the <fen>Illicit_organization</fen> is concealed by (the activities of) the <fen>Front</fen> .
The time at which the deceptive activity occurs
The place where the fronting occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who acts in a misleading way to create the impression that they are a particular individual or type of <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The type or individual that the <fen>Agent</fen> gives the impression of being.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> impersonates the <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> gives the impression that they are the <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>His speech</fex> convinced me to join the Peace Corps.
You haven't convinced me <fex>about that yet</fex>.
The top <fex>shelf</fex> of the bookcase was lying on the floor.
The show takes place in the West wing <fex>of the White House</fex>.
He lives in the <fex><t>backwoods</t></fex> of Canada.
